---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-asia-specific', text: 'Why Asia-Specific', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'country-considerations', text: 'Country Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-quality', text: 'Healthcare Quality', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Thailand Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
  { title: 'Singapore Insurance', href: '/countries/singapore/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Multi-Country Insurance', href: '/best/multi-country-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'asiaNetwork', header: 'Asia Network' },
  { key: 'thailand', header: 'Thailand Coverage' },
  { key: 'singapore', header: 'Singapore Access' },
  { key: 'pricing', header: 'Asia Pricing' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', asiaNetwork: 'Excellent', thailand: 'Strong network', singapore: 'Full access', pricing: 'Mid-range' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', asiaNetwork: 'Excellent', thailand: 'Strong network', singapore: 'Full access', pricing: 'Premium' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', asiaNetwork: 'Good', thailand: 'Good network', singapore: 'Good access', pricing: 'Competitive' },
  { provider: 'Pacific Prime', asiaNetwork: 'Excellent', thailand: 'Specialists', singapore: 'Local expert', pricing: 'Mid-range' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', asiaNetwork: 'Good', thailand: 'Basic network', singapore: 'Limited', pricing: 'Budget' },
];

const countryColumns = [
  { key: 'country', header: 'Country' },
  { key: 'healthcare', header: 'Healthcare Quality' },
  { key: 'cost', header: 'Cost Level' },
  { key: 'expats', header: 'Expat Accessibility' },
];

const countryRows = [
  { country: 'Singapore', healthcare: 'World-class', cost: 'Very expensive', expats: 'Excellent (English)' },
  { country: 'Thailand', healthcare: 'Very good (private)', cost: 'Moderate', expats: 'Excellent (medical tourism)' },
  { country: 'Malaysia', healthcare: 'Good (private)', cost: 'Affordable', expats: 'Good (English common)' },
  { country: 'Vietnam', healthcare: 'Improving', cost: 'Low', expats: 'Moderate (language barrier)' },
  { country: 'Indonesia', healthcare: 'Variable', cost: 'Low-moderate', expats: 'Moderate (Bali better)' },
  { country: 'Japan', healthcare: 'Excellent', cost: 'High', expats: 'Challenging (language)' },
  { country: 'Philippines', healthcare: 'Good (Manila)', cost: 'Low', expats: 'Good (English)' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Expat Insurance for Asia 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance optimized for Asian expats. Find plans with strong networks in Thailand, Singapore, Vietnam, and across Southeast Asia."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance for Asia"
  subheadline="Living in Asia? Here are the international health insurance plans with the best regional networks, from Bangkok's world-class hospitals to emerging healthcare markets."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-asia-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Asia</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers have the best coverage for expats in Asia:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌏</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Asia Overall</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Excellent Southeast Asia network with strong presence in Thailand, Singapore, and beyond.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏥</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Premium Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Access to top hospitals across Asia including Bumrungrad, Mount Elizabeth, and more.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇸🇬</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Local Expertise</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Pacific Prime</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Asia-headquartered broker with deep regional expertise and local support.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💰</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Budget Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Affordable Asia coverage for budget-conscious expats and digital nomads.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="why-asia-specific">Why Asia-Specific Insurance Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Asia has unique healthcare considerations:
  </p>

  <h3>Huge Quality Variation</h3>
  <p>
    Healthcare quality varies dramatically across Asia:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Singapore and Bangkok have world-class facilities</li>
    <li>Rural areas may have limited care</li>
    <li>Private vs public quality gap is significant</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation may be needed from some locations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Tourism Hubs</h3>
  <p>
    Some Asian countries are medical tourism destinations:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Thailand: Bumrungrad, Bangkok Hospital are world-renowned</li>
    <li>Singapore: Mount Elizabeth, Gleneagles top Asian facilities</li>
    <li>Malaysia: Growing medical tourism industry</li>
    <li>India: Specialized procedures at fraction of Western cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Hotspots</h3>
  <p>
    Asia attracts many digital nomads:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Thailand (Chiang Mai, Bangkok, islands)</li>
    <li>Vietnam (Ho Chi Minh City, Da Nang)</li>
    <li>Bali, Indonesia</li>
    <li>Philippines (various islands)</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Moving to Asia?"
    description="Compare plans with strong Asian healthcare networks."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Asia Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best for Asia Overall</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global has an excellent network across Southeast Asia.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong Thailand network (Bumrungrad, Bangkok Hospital)</li>
    <li>Full Singapore hospital access</li>
    <li>Good Malaysia, Vietnam, Philippines coverage</li>
    <li>24/7 support in Asian time zones</li>
    <li>Direct billing at major hospitals</li>
    <li>Modular plans for customization</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Mid-range to premium pricing. Network strongest in major cities. Excellent choice for most Asian expats.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Premium Asian Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers access to the best hospitals across Asia.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to top-tier Asian hospitals</li>
    <li>Bumrungrad, Mount Elizabeth, Raffles in network</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li>Strong emergency evacuation</li>
    <li>Excellent service</li>
    <li>Good for families</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Worth it for access to best facilities. May be overkill in lower-cost countries.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Pacific Prime — Local Asian Expertise</h3>
  <p>
    Pacific Prime is an Asia-based broker with deep regional knowledge.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Headquartered in Hong Kong and Singapore</li>
    <li>Deep understanding of Asian healthcare markets</li>
    <li>Can compare multiple insurers</li>
    <li>Local support in Asian time zones</li>
    <li>Expertise in specific countries</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Broker, not insurer—works with multiple carriers. Good for getting tailored advice on Asian insurance options.</p>

  <h3>IMG Global — Budget Asia Option</h3>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers affordable coverage for Asian expats.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lower premiums than competitors</li>
    <li>Adequate network in major Asian cities</li>
    <li>Good for digital nomads on budget</li>
    <li>Multiple plan tiers</li>
    <li>Covers major medical needs</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Smaller network than premium insurers. Less direct billing. Best for budget-conscious healthy individuals.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/img-global">Read our full IMG Global review</a></p>

  <h2 id="country-considerations">Country-by-Country Considerations</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={countryColumns} rows={countryRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Thailand</h3>
  <p>
    Thailand has excellent private healthcare:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Bumrungrad, Bangkok Hospital are world-class</li>
    <li>Medical tourism hub with English-speaking staff</li>
    <li>Affordable compared to Western countries</li>
    <li>Good for elective procedures too</li>
    <li>Insurance highly recommended despite low costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Singapore</h3>
  <p>
    Singapore has world-class but expensive healthcare:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Mount Elizabeth, Gleneagles, Raffles top facilities</li>
    <li>Very expensive without insurance</li>
    <li>Mandatory insurance for employment passes</li>
    <li>Excellent English throughout healthcare system</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Vietnam</h3>
  <p>
    Vietnam healthcare is improving but variable:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Good private hospitals in Ho Chi Minh City and Hanoi</li>
    <li>FV Hospital, Vinmec popular with expats</li>
    <li>Language can be a barrier</li>
    <li>May need evacuation for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Indonesia (Bali)</h3>
  <p>
    Bali has better healthcare than most of Indonesia:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BIMC, Siloam serve expat community</li>
    <li>Serious cases often evacuated to Singapore</li>
    <li>Insurance with evacuation important</li>
    <li>Variable quality outside Bali</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Find the Right Plan for Your Country"
    description="Different Asian countries have different insurance needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="healthcare-quality">Healthcare Quality Across Asia</h2>

  <h3>Top-Tier Facilities</h3>
  <p>
    Asia has some world-class hospitals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bumrungrad (Bangkok):</strong> 1.1 million patients/year, many international</li>
    <li><strong>Mount Elizabeth (Singapore):</strong> JCI-accredited, multi-specialty</li>
    <li><strong>Raffles Hospital (Singapore):</strong> Comprehensive medical center</li>
    <li><strong>Gleneagles (Singapore/Malaysia):</strong> Regional hospital group</li>
    <li><strong>Bangkok Hospital Group:</strong> Multiple Thai locations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>When Evacuation May Be Needed</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Remote locations in any country</li>
    <li>Complex surgeries in developing countries</li>
    <li>Specialty care not available locally</li>
    <li>Quality concerns in smaller cities</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Tropical Disease Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Asia has specific health risks:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Dengue fever (widespread in tropical areas)</li>
    <li>Malaria (some regions)</li>
    <li>Typhoid (food/water safety)</li>
    <li>Japanese encephalitis</li>
    <li>Good insurance covers treatment for all these</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Asia-only coverage cheaper than worldwide?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, typically 20-40% cheaper than worldwide plans. Asia (excluding Japan) has lower healthcare costs than the US or Europe, so insurers price accordingly. Consider your travel patterns before limiting coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Which Asian countries have the best healthcare?</h3>
  <p>
    Singapore has the best overall healthcare in Asia, followed by Thailand and Malaysia for private care. Japan and South Korea also have excellent systems but with language barriers. Quality varies significantly within countries—major cities have better facilities.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need insurance in Thailand? Healthcare is cheap.</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. While routine care is affordable, serious illness or accidents can still cost tens of thousands. ICU stays, surgeries, and evacuation can wipe out savings. The low cost of Thai insurance makes it worth having.
  </p>

  <h3>What about local Asian insurers vs international?</h3>
  <p>
    Local insurers may be cheaper but often have limitations: smaller networks, language barriers in claims, coverage only in one country, and less experience with expat needs. International insurers offer portability and broader coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Is evacuation coverage important in Asia?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, especially outside major cities. While Bangkok and Singapore have world-class care, remote areas or smaller countries may require evacuation to a medical hub. Make sure your plan includes adequate evacuation coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use Thailand as a medical tourism destination while insured elsewhere?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes, if Thailand is within your coverage area. Many expats living elsewhere travel to Thailand for elective procedures. Check your policy covers the specific treatment and location.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Healthcare quality and costs vary by location and change over time. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify current coverage and provider networks directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
